radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bilateral dependent atelectasis, dilated appendix up to 1.4 cm with a calcified appendicolith at its base, significant fat stranding around the appendix, no drainable fluid collection or free air, normal liver, gallbladder with a punctate calcified gallstone, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys without lesions or hydronephrosis, no evidence of bowel obstruction, a few sigmoid diverticula, normal aorta, circumambient left renal vein, scattered retroperitoneal and mesenteric lymph nodes not enlarged, no ascites, pelvic free fluid, and an enlarged prostate.
